This is just my personal vim config.

Windows:

  mklink /D %HOMEDRIVE%\%HOMEPATH%\vimfiles path_to_repo\vimconfig\vimfiles
  mklink %HOMEDRIVE%\%HOMEPATH%\_vimrc path_to_repo\vimconfig\_vimrc
  mklink %HOMEDRIVE%\%HOMEPATH%\_gvimrc path_to_repo\vimconfig\_gvimrc

N.B. I'm not 100% sure that it's correct from a Windows-perspective that I'm using %HOMEDRIVE%\%HOMEPATH% instead of %USERPROFILE%, but as far as I can tell, this is what Vim actually uses for setting $HOME.

Mac/Unix:

  ln -s path_to_repo\vimconfig\vimfiles ~\vimfiles
  ln -s path_to_repo\vimconfig\.vimrc ~\_vimrc
  ln -s path_to_repo\vimconfig\.gvimrc ~\_gvimrc

